data: The Seabeast is out there somewhere. And so is safety. Go find one of them. But before you depart, choose your first mate.
Your first mate settles in and asks where to next.

You get a bad feeling. You scan the surrounding waters for the tell tale dark shadows just below the surface that preempt an attack from the depths. But this time the source for concern isn't from below the water but speeding just above it. Four armed men are quickly approaching straight towards your boat. YOUR boat! It's not looking good. These men are definitely pirates.

The radio buzzes to life.  The voice of a middle aged man. A documentary producer who explains that the crew for his hit show "Shark Chasers" is stranded on a small, tide reliant island off the coast while they were shooting an episode of his hit show. He begs you to rescue the crew of his hit show before high tide returns and erases the island, and in turn, his hit show.

You come upon a dingy in the open sea. Miraculously, there is still a man alive on the raft. But there are also signs that there may have been a struggle on board. Scraps of bright colored clothing that don’t match the man’s clothes and dried blood on a second life jacket. You ask the man if there was anyone with him and he says no one else survived when their ship sunk.

You receive a distress call from the Nautilus, captained by one of your bitter rivals, Captain Pratt. The contents of the message are unclear, but you do manage to extract a set of coordinates from the crackling broadcast
Uh oh ... the pirates are back! This time on jet skis!

You begin to hear the unmistakable sounds of a bull horn, and. . . a drum circle? You grab your binoculars and spy a janky, reconfigured fishing boat bearing down on you. It is covered in bright spray paint and has a jury-rigged harpoon gun on the bow. They are Green Peace Guerillas,  packing potato guns. Their leader screams into the bull horn: “Meat is MURDER! Leave the fishes BE! Prepare to be boarded!”
A pod of dolphins swims alongside the boat.

A small propeller plane approaches, flying quite low over the open water. It’s difficult to tell through binoculars, but it appears that something is being thrown from the plane. Whatever it is splashes down less than a kilometer away.

A beautiful melody begins to swell over the sounds of wind and chop. The most beautiful melody you’ve ever heard, in fact, strange and irresistible. It seems to be echoing from out of a nearby cove, draped in morning fog.
Hmm ... this looks like it could be a good fishing spot. Want to sit a spell and see what we can catch?
Medical supplies are floating in the water.

A good host serves food, and your guests approve, flipping into the air, clicking and chattering. After a moment, they pull ahead of the boat and turn several degrees to starboard. Curious. Should you follow?

You skillfully pilot the boat between craggy rocks once hidden by mist and enter the cove. The fog begins to lift and you’re able to see the source of the sound. It appears to be an island concert. A small stage has been erected and a small crowd sways to the sound.

You skillfully pilot the boat between craggy rocks once hidden by mist and enter the cove. The fog begins to lift and you’re able to see the source of the sound. A woman in a billowing gown is aimlessly walking on the beach barefoot, singing sweetly. She doesn’t seem to notice you approaching.
Cristo ... what a kid? Seriously? Desperate times.
Try to outrun them. It doesn't look hopeful but it may be your only chance
Decline. You’re not a fan of the show.
Jet skis can’t be an effective transport for pirates. Voice your concern to them.
Whatever this is, you want no part of it and hold your course.
Follow the music to its source.
Let's grab them and try not to think about what has recently taken place here.
No, you have no time for detours.
Drop anchor and take in the show.
Bring the boat in closer and see if the woman needs help.
Viktoria ... hmm big gap in work history. Skilled with a knife?
Fight. The pirates will learn to regret their life choices
Agree, but only after you've made sure the Seabeast isn't in the area.
Give him food and water, but ask that he stay on his raft and tow him to the nearest port.
Ask them to rate their distress on a scale from 1 to 10, 10 being the most distressed, 1 being the least distressed
Prepare to be boarded. They will surely be on their way once you’ve explained that you aren’t a fishing vessel.
Seems suspicious. See if you can raise the Coast Guard on the radio.
Try to resist and continue on.
It's the ocean's now. Let's move on.
You aren’t sure what you were expecting, but you really don’t have the time to stay.
Agree to drop everything and head out there.
Cut him loose and pray that no one else finds him before the sea swallows him whole.
Suspend all duties and head to the coordiantes
Sirens! It must be! Stick smelt in your ears and push the throttle.
Ask [FM] if they've heard of Shark Chasers.
Draw the fish they want to "protect with chum"
Watch a few episodes of Shark Chasers before deciding what to do.
